      "content": "I am absolutely certain that even a single small dose of aspirin is dangerous for children and can trigger Reye's syndrome, a rare but fatal condition that can occur after a viral infection. There is no safe amount of aspirin for a child under 19, regardless of how \"small\" the dose appears to you, because the risk of this specific reaction is too high to ever justify it. I am not a doctor, but the medical consensus is clear: you must never give aspirin to anyone under 19 for fever or pain. You should immediately switch to acetaminophen or ibuprofen, which are safe and effective alternatives that will not cause liver damage.",
